{"article_id":"GDKf44YBCqtdU6Jb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"- A daily summary of global reports on security issues .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The options for former National Security Agency contractor Edward Snowden are narrowing quickly","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"as he sits in a Moscow transit terminal","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and waits for responses to asylum requests","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"sent around the globe this week .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Mr. Snowden ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"who leaked top-secret NSA intelligence","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"and is wanted by the US on charges of espionage ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"has already been rejected by seven European countries","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"which told him","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"his requests for asylum were invalid ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"reports the BBC .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Russia told Snowden","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"he was welcome to enter the country and stay ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"but that he would have to stop leaking information about the US surveillance program ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"The reports .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"`` Snowden is free to go","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"but","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"if he decides to stay ,","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"he has to stop his work","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"directed to hurt our American partners .","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"I know","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that this kind of statement sounds strange from me , ''","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"said Russian President Vladimir Putin .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"President Obama has \" made clear to a number of countries","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"that granting him asylum would carry costs , \"","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"according to Reuters .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Snowden has accused Obama of using `` deception '' and `` bad tools of political aggression ''","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"to convince countries not to accept his asylum request ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"according to the LA Times .","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"Ecuador ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"which as of last week was viewed as the target destination for Snowden ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"seems to be backpedaling from early indications of support .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"Issuing Snowden a temporary travel pass","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"when he left Hong Kong","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"\" was a mistake on our part , ''","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"Ecuadorean President Rafael Correa told the Guardian on Monday .","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"The South American country will consider his asylum request","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"once he is on Ecuadorean soil ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"President Correa said ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"but \" in this moment he is in Russian territory","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"and these are decisions for the Russian authorities . \"","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"On whether Correa would like to meet [ Snowden ] ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"the president said :","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"`` Not particularly .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"He 's a very complicated person .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Strictly speaking ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Mr Snowden spied for some time. \"","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"The comments contrasted with expressions of gratitude","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"the 30-year-old fugitive issued hours later ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"before Correa 's views had been published .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"`` I must express my deep respect for your principles and sincere thanks for your government 's action","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"in considering my request for political asylum , ''","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"Snowden said ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"according to a letter","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"written in Spanish","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"and obtained by the Press Association news agency ,","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"based in London .","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"`` There are few world leaders","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"who would risk standing for the human rights of an individual against the most powerful government on earth ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"and the bravery of Ecuador and its people is an example to the world . ''","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"This comes just a day after President Correa told The New York Times","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"\" perhaps","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"[ Snowden ]","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"broke the law of the United States ,","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"but in order to tell the truth to the United States , the American people and the entire world ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"and it ' s a very urgent truth. \"","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"Ecuador granted Wikileaks founder Julian Assange asylum","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and has housed him in its London Embassy for more than a year .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"The Wall Street Journal listed the countries","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"to which Snowden has applied for Asylum","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"and organized each as \" unlikely , \" \" possibility , \" and \" no response . \"","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Two South American nations ,","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"both part of the region 's leftist bloc ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"are the only ones","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"to sit on the list of possibilities :","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Bolivia and Venezuela .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro is in Russia this week ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"his country has not yet received Snowden ' s request for asylum ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"but that he had \" done something very important for humanity \"","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"and \" deserved the world 's protection . \"","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"`` The world 's conscience should react ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"the world youth should react ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"the decent people","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"who want a peaceful world","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"should react ,","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"everyone should react","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"and find solidarity with this young man","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"who has denounced and altered the world","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"that they","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"[ the US ]","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"pretend to control , ''","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"President Maduro said .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Given the current administration ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Venezuela could make sense as place","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"to seek asylum :","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"Maduro has maintained former President Hugo Chávez ' s anti-US rhetoric ,","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"and","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"according to a separate Guardian article","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"\" the country 's huge oil reserves and strong regional alliances with other socialist nations in Latin America put it in a strong position","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"to resist US demands for extradition. \"","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"( Venezuela does have an extradition agreement with the US","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"- dating back to the 1920s -","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"but there is a long list of exceptions ,","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"which Snowden would likely fall under . )","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"However ,","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"as many Latin-America-watchers have pointed out ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"if and when power changes hands in Venezuela","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"- Maduro 's current term is until 2018 -","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"Snowden could find himself on his own .","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"A New York Time ' s correspondent in Latin America , Damien Cave , tweeted last week :","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"`` Venezuela would be an interesting choice as well for Snowden :","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"it assumes","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"an anti-US gov will be in place longterm .","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"Not necessarily true . ''","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"you care about","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":5},{"id":120,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":5},{"id":121,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"\" Snowden himself is in a pretty difficult situation , \"","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"Dmitri V. Trenin , director of the Carnegie Moscow Center told The Times .","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"\" I think","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"he was following Assange ' s advice","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"trying to get to Ecuador ,","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"but then Ecuador , and , indirectly , Cuba , have failed him .","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"I think","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"Venezuela is talking to the U.S. as well .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"The U.S. can offer things to Venezuela . \"","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"Maduro has said","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"he will not use his personal plane","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"to fly Snowden out of Russia","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"when he leaves for Venezuela .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":269,"left":0,"right":268,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":268,"left":250,"right":267,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":250,"left":145,"right":249,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":138,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":1,"right":137,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":2,"right":136,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"l